Key Match Events: Nikola Jokic scored nine points in overtime to secure the win for Denver.
Victor Wembanyama was scoreless and without a rebound in overtime.
Michael Porter Jr. added 28 points and 10 rebounds for Denver.
Harrison Barnes scored 22 points and Devin Vassell 19 for San Antonio.
Zach Collins and Russell Westbrook each received a technical foul in the first quarter after taunting one another.
Post-Match Reflections: Nikola Jokic praised Victor Wembanyama, believing he will be'remembered forever' in the league.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The teams split the home-and-home series on consecutive nights.
San Antonio had won two straight before this game.
